cs.RO, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on human-robot interaction and collaboration.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper evaluates the perceived performance of the human-robot team.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper uses Bayesian inference for goal prediction.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses Bayesian inference, which is a type of machine learning.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the need for robots to adapt to human collaborators in order to improve safety and end-user adoption.
